Global Peripheral Anesthesia Disposable Devices Market Insights
Peripheral Anesthesia Disposable Devices Market size was valued at USD 2.5 Billion in 2022 and is projected to reach USD 4.0 Billion by 2030, growing at a CAGR of 7.5% from 2024 to 2030.

Peripheral Anesthesia Disposable Devices Market Overview
The global peripheral anesthesia disposable devices market was valued at approximately USD 3.2 billion in 2024 and is projected to grow at a CAGR of 6.1% during the forecast period of 2025-2032. This market includes devices used for local anesthesia in peripheral nerve blocks and offers a wide range of products such as needles, catheters, and injection systems. The rise in surgical procedures, advancements in healthcare technology, and increasing adoption of minimally invasive surgeries are the key growth drivers. As a result, the market is witnessing growing demand for these disposable devices globally.

